00:38.420 --> 00:41.400
CHAPTER XXIII The Gospel of Luke

00:42.680 --> 00:46.700
And a whole multitude of them arose and led him on to Pilate.

00:46.980 --> 00:49.000
And they began to accuse him, saying,

00:49.340 --> 00:52.120
We found this fellow perverting the nation,

00:52.420 --> 00:54.420
and forbidding to give tribute to Caesar,

00:55.020 --> 00:57.940
saying that he himself is Christ, a King.

00:59.420 --> 01:01.360
And Pilate asked him, saying,

01:02.260 --> 01:03.980
Art thou the King of the Jews?

01:04.820 --> 01:06.640
And he answered him and said,

01:07.520 --> 01:08.860
Thou sayest it.

01:09.600 --> 01:12.900
Then said Pilate to the chief priests and to the people,

01:13.720 --> 01:15.760
I find no fault in this man.

01:16.780 --> 01:19.240
And they were the more fierce, saying,

01:19.560 --> 01:23.000
He stirth up the people, teaching throughout all Jewry,

01:23.280 --> 01:25.380
beginning from Galilee to this place.

01:26.680 --> 01:31.620
When Pilate heard of Galilee, he asked whether the man were a Galilean.

01:32.460 --> 01:37.140
And as soon as he knew that he belonged unto Herod's jurisdiction,

01:37.800 --> 01:43.300
he sent him to Herod, who himself also was at Jerusalem at that time.

01:44.840 --> 01:48.920
And when Herod saw Jesus, he was exceeding glad,

01:49.160 --> 01:52.920
for he was desirous to see him of a long season,

01:53.120 --> 01:55.620
because he had heard many things of him,

01:56.040 --> 01:59.520
and he hoped to have seen some miracle done by him.

02:00.580 --> 02:03.580
Then he questioned with him in many words,

02:04.120 --> 02:05.860
but he answered him nothing.

02:06.660 --> 02:11.040
And the chief priests and scribes stood and vehemently accused him.

02:12.240 --> 02:17.480
And Herod with his men of war set him at naught, and mocked him,

02:17.780 --> 02:22.360
and arrayed him in a gorgeous robe, and sent him again to Pilate.

02:23.440 --> 02:27.860
And the same day Pilate and Herod were made friends together,

02:28.800 --> 02:31.760
for before they were at enmity between themselves.

02:33.680 --> 02:38.420
And Pilate, when he had called together the chief priests and the rulers

02:38.420 --> 02:40.820
and the people, said unto them,

02:42.320 --> 02:46.560
Ye have brought this man unto me as one that perverteth the people.

02:47.100 --> 02:51.080
And behold, I, having examined him before you,

02:51.300 --> 02:56.120
have found no fault in this man touching those things, whereof ye accuse him.

02:56.700 --> 03:00.760
No, nor yet Herod, for I sent you to him,

03:01.220 --> 03:04.460
and lo, nothing worthy of death is done unto him.

03:04.460 --> 03:08.220
I will therefore chastise him and release him,

03:09.260 --> 03:13.980
for of necessity he must release one unto them at the feast.

03:14.800 --> 03:17.620
And they cried out all at once, saying,

03:18.040 --> 03:22.300
Away with this man, and release unto us Barabbas,

03:22.700 --> 03:28.840
who for a certain sedition made in the city and for murder was cast into prison.

03:30.120 --> 03:34.120
Pilate therefore, willing to release Jesus, spake again to them,

03:34.120 --> 03:39.020
but they cried, saying, Crucify him, crucify him.

03:40.260 --> 03:45.080
And he said unto them the third time, Why, what evil hath he done?

03:45.520 --> 03:51.820
I have found no cause of death in him, I will therefore chastise him and let him go.

03:52.460 --> 03:57.480
And they were instant with loud voices requiring that he might be crucified,

03:58.200 --> 04:02.520
and the voices of them and of the chief priests prevailed.

04:03.340 --> 04:07.620
And Pilate gave sentence, that it should be as they required.

04:08.640 --> 04:14.240
And he released unto them him that for sedition and murder was cast into prison,

04:14.620 --> 04:18.840
whom they had desired. But he delivered Jesus to their will.

04:19.860 --> 04:25.440
And as they led him away, they laid hold upon one Simon, a Cyrenian,

04:25.820 --> 04:30.320
coming out of the country, and on him they laid the cross,

04:30.320 --> 04:37.120
that he might bear it after Jesus. And there followed him a great company of people,

04:37.340 --> 04:40.960
and of women, which also bewailed and lamented him.

04:41.920 --> 04:49.400
But Jesus, turning unto them, said, Daughters of Jerusalem, weep not for me,

04:49.940 --> 04:55.620
but weep for yourselves and for your children. For behold, the days are coming,

04:55.620 --> 05:00.960
in the which they shall say, Blessed are the barren, and the wombs that never bear,

05:01.360 --> 05:07.060
and the paps which never gave suck. Then shall they begin to say to the mountains,

05:07.480 --> 05:14.780
Fall on us, and to the hills cover us. For if they do these things in a green tree,

05:15.220 --> 05:21.900
what shall be done in the dry? And there were also two other

05:23.020 --> 05:30.080
malefactors, led with him to be put to death. And when they were come to the place,

05:30.360 --> 05:36.260
which is called Calvary, there they crucified him, and the malefactors,

05:36.260 --> 05:39.760
one on the right hand, and the other on the left.

05:40.920 --> 05:48.180
Then said Jesus, Father, forgive them, for they know not what they do.

05:49.500 --> 05:57.020
And they parted his reinment, and cast lots, and the people stood beholding.

05:58.720 --> 06:05.480
And the rulers also with them derided him, saying, He saved others, let him save himself,

06:05.600 --> 06:11.880
if he be Christ, the Chosen of God. And the soldiers also mocked him,

06:11.880 --> 06:18.580
coming to him and offering him vinegar, and saying, If thou be the King of the Jews,

06:18.760 --> 06:26.060
save thyself. And a superscription also was written over him in letters of Greek,

06:26.560 --> 06:31.780
and Latin, and Hebrew, This is the King of the Jews.

06:33.560 --> 06:39.320
And one of the malefactors which were hanged railed on him, saying, If thou be Christ,

06:39.320 --> 06:45.760
save thyself and us. But the other answering rebuked him, saying,

06:46.620 --> 06:54.180
Dost not thou fear God, seeing thou art in the same condemnation? And we indeed justly,

06:54.300 --> 07:00.680
for we receive the due reward of our deeds. But this man hath done nothing amiss.

07:01.620 --> 07:08.260
And he said unto Jesus, Lord, remember me when thou comest into thy kingdom.

07:09.720 --> 07:18.820
And Jesus said unto him, Verily I say unto thee, Today shalt thou be with me in paradise.

07:21.020 --> 07:28.940
And it was about the sixth hour, and there was a darkness over all the earth until the ninth hour.

07:29.820 --> 07:35.100
And the sun was darkened, and the veil of the temple was rent in the midst.

07:35.100 --> 07:43.780
And when Jesus had cried with a loud voice, he said, Father, into thy hands I commend my

07:43.780 --> 07:55.680
spirit. And having said thus, he gave up the ghost. Now when the centurion saw what was done,

07:56.300 --> 08:03.920
he glorified God, saying, Certainly this was a righteous man. And all the people that came

08:03.920 --> 08:10.580
together to that site, beholding the things which were done, smote their breasts and returned.

08:12.740 --> 08:18.780
And all his acquaintance and the women that followed him from Galilee stood afar off,

08:19.260 --> 08:27.460
beholding these things. And behold, there was a man named Joseph, a counselor,

08:28.100 --> 08:36.680
and he was a good man and a just. The same had not consented to the council and deed of them,

08:37.220 --> 08:44.800
he was of Arimathea, a city of the Jews, who also himself waited for the kingdom of God.

08:46.060 --> 08:54.360
This man went on the pilot and begged the body of Jesus, and he took it down and wrapped it in linen

08:54.360 --> 09:02.020
and laid it in a sepulcher that was hewn in stone, wherein never man before was laid.

09:03.620 --> 09:10.400
And that day was the preparation, and the Sabbath drew on. And the women also,

09:10.820 --> 09:18.320
which came with him from Galilee, followed after and beheld the sepulcher and how his

09:18.320 --> 09:26.080
body was laid. And they returned and prepared spices and ointments and rested the Sabbath

09:26.080 --> 09:32.640
day according to the commandment. Chapter 24

09:32.640 --> 09:40.200
Now upon the first day of the week, very early in the morning, they came unto the sepulcher,

09:40.700 --> 09:47.120
bringing the spices which they had prepared, and certain others with them. And they found

09:47.120 --> 09:53.540
the stone rolled away from the sepulcher. And they entered in, and found not the body

09:53.540 --> 10:00.360
of the Lord Jesus. And it came to pass, as they were much perplexed thereabout, behold,

10:00.840 --> 10:08.200
two men stood by them in shining garments. And as they were afraid, and bowed down their faces to

10:08.200 --> 10:15.860
the earth, they said unto them, Why seek ye the living among the dead? He is not here,

10:15.860 --> 10:22.720
but is risen. Remember how he spake unto you when he was yet in Galilee, saying,

10:23.000 --> 10:28.480
The son of man must be delivered into the hands of sinful men, and be crucified,

10:28.900 --> 10:36.720
and the third day rise again. And they remembered his words, and returned from the sepulcher,

10:37.280 --> 10:41.360
and told all these things unto the eleven, and to all the rest.

10:42.540 --> 10:51.000
It was Mary Magdalene, and Joanna, and Mary the mother of James, and other women that were with

10:51.000 --> 10:58.500
them, which told these things unto the apostles. And their words seemed to them as idle tales,

10:58.860 --> 11:06.200
and they believed them not. Then arose Peter, and ran unto the sepulcher, and stooping down,

11:06.200 --> 11:13.000
he beheld the linen clothes laid by themselves, and departed, wondering in himself

11:13.000 --> 11:20.780
at that which was come to pass. And behold, two of them went that same day to a village

11:20.780 --> 11:28.620
called Emmaus, which was from Jerusalem about three score furlongs, and they talked together

11:28.620 --> 11:36.020
of all these things which had happened. And it came to pass that while they communed together,

11:36.200 --> 11:45.360
and reasoned, Jesus himself drew near, and went with them. But their eyes were holden that they

11:45.360 --> 11:53.600
should not know him. And he said unto them, What manner of communications are these, that ye have

11:53.600 --> 12:01.440
one to another, as ye walk and are sad? And the one of them, whose name was Cleopas, answering,

12:01.440 --> 12:08.400
said unto him, Art thou only a stranger in Jerusalem, and hast not known the things

12:08.400 --> 12:15.500
which are come to pass there in these days? And he said unto them, What things?

12:16.500 --> 12:23.280
And they said unto him, Concerning Jesus of Nazareth, which was a prophet, mighty in deed

12:23.280 --> 12:29.520
and word before God and all the people, and how the chief priests and our rulers delivered him to

12:29.520 --> 12:37.420
condemn to death, and have crucified him. But we trusted that it had been he which should have

12:37.420 --> 12:45.240
redeemed Israel. And beside all this, today is the third day since these things were done.

12:46.080 --> 12:52.240
Yea, and certain women also of our company made us astonished which were early at the sepulcher.

12:52.940 --> 12:59.640
And when they found not his body, they came saying that they had also seen a vision of angels

12:59.640 --> 13:06.980
which said that he was alive. And certain of them which were with us went to the sepulcher

13:06.980 --> 13:12.440
and found it even so as the women had said, but him they saw not.

13:14.360 --> 13:21.560
Then he said unto them, O fools and slow of heart to believe all that the prophets have spoken.

13:22.240 --> 13:27.600
Ought not Christ to have suffered these things and to enter into his glory?

13:29.240 --> 13:35.700
And beginning at Moses and all the prophets, he expounded unto them in all the scriptures

13:35.700 --> 13:42.840
the things concerning himself. And they drew nigh unto the village whither they went,

13:43.460 --> 13:49.020
and he made as though he would have gone further. But they constrained him saying,

13:49.020 --> 13:58.560
Abide with us, for it is toward evening, and the day is far spent, and he went in to Terry with them.

13:59.440 --> 14:07.060
And it came to pass, as he sat at meet with them, he took bread, and blessed it,

14:07.960 --> 14:15.980
and break, and gave to them. And their eyes were opened, and they knew him,

14:17.000 --> 14:25.740
and he vanished out of their sight. And they said one to another, Did not our heart burn within us

14:25.740 --> 14:30.760
while he talked with us by the way, and while he opened to us the scriptures?

14:31.900 --> 14:38.840
And they rose up the same hour, and returned to Jerusalem, and found the eleven gathered together,

14:39.380 --> 14:45.960
and them that were with them, saying, The Lord is risen indeed, and hath appeared to some of us,

14:45.960 --> 14:54.280
Simon. And they told what things were done in the way, and how he was known of them

14:54.280 --> 15:03.140
in breaking of bread. And as they thus spake, Jesus himself stood in the midst of them,

15:03.580 --> 15:10.360
and saith unto them, Peace be unto you. But they were terrified, and affrighted,

15:10.360 --> 15:18.700
and supposed that they had seen a spirit. And he said unto them, Why are ye troubled?

15:19.200 --> 15:26.400
And why do thoughts arise in your hearts? Behold my hands and my feet, that it is I myself.

15:26.900 --> 15:33.340
Handle me, and see, for a spirit hath not flesh and bones, as ye see me have.

15:34.620 --> 15:42.120
And when he had thus spoken, he showed them his hands and his feet. And while they yet believed

15:42.120 --> 15:49.900
not for joy, and wondered, he said unto them, Have ye any meat? And they gave him a piece

15:49.900 --> 15:56.400
of a broiled fish, and of a honeycomb. And he took it, and did eat before them.

15:57.180 --> 16:04.440
And he said unto them, These are the words which I spake unto you while I was yet with you,

16:04.720 --> 16:10.460
that all things must be fulfilled which were written in the law of Moses, and in the prophets,

16:10.800 --> 16:18.580
and in the Psalms concerning me. Then opened he their understanding that they might understand

16:18.580 --> 16:27.120
the scriptures. And said unto them, Thus it is written, and thus it behoved Christ to suffer,

16:27.460 --> 16:34.200
and to rise from the dead the third day. And that repentance and remission of sins should be

16:34.200 --> 16:41.640
preached in his name among all nations, beginning at Jerusalem. And ye are witnesses of these things.

16:42.400 --> 16:49.500
And, behold, I send the promise of my Father upon you, but tarry ye in the city of Jerusalem

16:49.500 --> 16:58.940
until ye be endued with power from on high. And he led them out as far as to Bethany,

16:59.540 --> 17:06.460
and he lifted up his hands and blessed them. And it came to pass, while he blessed them,

17:06.460 --> 17:14.580
he was parted from them, and carried up into heaven. And they worshiped him, and returned

17:14.580 --> 17:23.700
to Jerusalem with great joy, and were continually in the temple, praising and blessing God. Amen.

17:27.240 --> 17:34.000
The end of the Gospel according to Saint Luke in the King James Version, also known as the

17:34.000 --> 17:40.440
Authorized Version, read by Father Zeile of Detroit, December, 2008.

